FTP Transaction

Resides at the application layer of the OSI Model

FTP transfers file using TCP ports 20 and 21

Port 21 = command channel on the FTP server
Port 20 = secondary port used to transfer data



FTP Reply codes

120 - Service ready in nn minutes
200 - Command okay
500 - Syntax Error
213 - File status


Active Request - The client initiates a data transfer
FTP server maintains state information
  Current directory and any user authentication


PASV Request - Preferred for clients behind a firewall and is more secure
  The client, not the server, initiates the transfer
Asks the server to accept a data connection on a new TCP port
  Server normally accepts with code 227
  Server provides a port



